description:
Bach's B minor mass is one of the most important works within the entirety of classical music: one of the most important works by arguably the world's greatest composer.  See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_in_B_minor

This is a very cold and majestic recording, as befits the music.  First-rate choir and orchestra, but slightly (very slightly) disappointing soloists.  Definitely superior overall to the oft-torrented Herreweghe recording.

